  "text": "The pass-through filter implementation follows the established Envoy HTTP filter extension patterns found in the source codebase. The core inheritance hierarchy is based on the StreamDecoderFilter interface defined in envoy/http/filter.h, which provides the abstract base class for HTTP request decoders. The filter implements three key decoding methods: decodeHeaders, decodeData, and decodeTrailers, returning appropriate status enums (FilterHeadersStatus::Continue, FilterDataStatus::Continue, FilterTrailersStatus::Continue) for each to allow request processing to continue downstream. The implementation pattern is directly modeled after existing filters such as BufferFilter (source/extensions/filters/http/buffer/buffer_filter.h and cc) and KillRequestFilter (source/extensions/filters/http/kill_request/kill_request_filter.h and cc), which both inherit from Http::StreamDecoderFilter and implement the same three decode methods. The factory registration pattern follows the NamedHttpFilterConfigFactory interface using the REGISTER_FACTORY macro, as demonstrated in source/extensions/filters/http/buffer/config.cc and source/extensions/filters/http/kill_request/kill_request_config.cc. The factory classes inherit from Common::FactoryBase (defined in source/extensions/filters/http/common/factory_base.h) and implement createFilterFactoryFromProtoTyped to instantiate filter objects via a lambda callback that adds the filter to the filter chain using addStreamDecoderFilter. The minimal pass-through implementation also references source/extensions/filters/http/common/pass_through_filter.h as a reference for the simplest form of a streaming decoder filter that passes all data through with Continue status, providing a template for implementation of filters that need to inspect but not modify request data."
}

